        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 4 at 5:01PM MDT by NWS Goodland KS</headline>
        <description>At 501 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 12
miles south of Tribune, moving north at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

This storm will remain over mainly rural areas of southeastern
Greeley County.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
